cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.CE, cs.CR 

This paper explores the use of Facebook Ads audience estimates for tracking non-communicable diseases around the world, which involves social media and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper also discusses the potential pitfalls of using Facebook's Marketing API, which falls under the category of cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy). The paper also involves analyzing demographic trends, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). Furthermore, the paper involves data analysis and modeling, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
